glosses: to step on, to stand on

examples.translation: I love stepping on fresh, powdery snow.

glosses: (of toddlers) to stand
to press (e.g. on a pedal, button, key)
to press (e.g. on a pedal, button, key)
(of a button, key, etc.) to function properly, to do what it's meant to

examples.text: Hiçbir sıkıntı yokken tuş basmamaya başladı.
examples.translation: For no good reason the key started not to work.
I did press it but the button didn't work.

glosses: to stuff

examples.translation: to stuff the cheese into the earthenware jar

glosses: to print, to publish, to press

examples.translation: We publish your book for free.

glosses: to cover

examples.text: Yollarını ot basmış olan bu büyük köşk.
examples.translation: This big mansion whose roads leaves have covered.

glosses: to impress, to imprint, to stamp (the tool used, such as a stamp or a seal, is the direct object; and the document which gets stamped is the indirect object)

examples.text: Şuraya başparmağını bas, dediler, ben de bastım.
examples.translation: They told me to impress (something) with my thumbprint and I did it.

glosses: to raid

examples.text: Ölen kızın intikamını almak için köyü basıp yakmış.
examples.translation: (I heard) he raided and burned down the village to revenge the girl who died.

glosses: to turn, to reach a certain age

examples.text: On dokuz yaşına yeni basmış, ürkek ve utangaç bir kızdım.
examples.translation: I was a shy and timid girl who just turned 19.

glosses: (of fog, smoke, etc.) to cover

examples.translation: Fog has covered the city, right before the evening.

glosses: to pump (to use a pump to move liquid or gas)

examples.translation: Pump was broken, it doesn't pump the water.

glosses: (of poultry) to incubate
to catch (to discover in an unpleasant state)

examples.translation: I caught my husband in bed with another woman.

glosses: to get overwhelmed by an emotion

examples.translation: Upon having problems arise, s/he started to sweat.

glosses: to lift an amount of weight, to do an exercise with said amount of load
(of motored vehicles) to be able to go at a said speed

examples.translation: How fast a BMW can go?

glosses: (usually in negative clauses) to comprehend

examples.translation: I just cannot comprehend what's happening.

glosses: to fuck

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish باصمق (basmak, “to press, print, coin money, tread on, overpower”), from Proto-Turkic *bas- (“to press”).
